# Conventional Commits

When creating commits, follow conventional commit format:

`<type>[optional scope]: <description>`

- Use `feat` for new features and `fix` for bug fixes.
- Use other standard types when appropriate: `docs`, `refactor`, `test`, `chore`, `perf`, `build`, `ci`.
- Keep description concise and action-oriented.
- Add body/footer only when needed for context or breaking changes.
- Mark breaking changes with `!` in the header or `BREAKING CHANGE:` in footer.
